<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6592&amp;p=64152#p64152"><![CDATA[
As for the "Game.nes" thing, it's really easy to use parameters supplied by the user. Look into <strong>argc</strong> and <strong>argv</strong> and you'll see how easy it is to use a name supplied by the user, instead of hardcoding it to "Game.nes" (this will also allow users to drag and drop the ROM on your program, making it very simple to use). About the output files, you could either hardcode them to something like "character.chr" and "program.prg" or do some light string manipulation and use the same name of the input file and change only the extension to "chr" and "prg".<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Jul 13, 2010 11:40 am</p><hr />
